issue.title: docs: Multi-port support for v1.17 GA

labels.name: pr/no-changelog
labels.description: PR does not need a corresponding .changelog entry

issue.body:
### Description

As part of the v1.17 GA release, multi-port has additional support for resource configurations. This PR adds documentation to explain the catalog APIs, adds reference documentation for the new resources, and updates usage instructions.

This PR is a work in progress. As of 10/26/23, the following pages are ready for review:

- [v1 catalog API]
- [v2 catalog API]
- [GRPCRoute resource configuration reference]

Because of the overlap in configuration specifications, I will implement suggestions you make to the GRPCRoute page to the corresponding sections of the HTTPRoute and TCPRoute pages.

This description will be updated with the latest drafts as they are available. The following section is a running list of the times that additional pages became available for review:

10/26/23 - 4:40 PM PST - Catalog pages and GRPCRoute configuration available

### Links

- [Initial draft](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1D3d_G4Hcteo6wNcauoyVIZpb5pjHfaQGB_E1kZ4nAa4/)
- [Examples repo](https://github.com/hashicorp/consul-catalog-v2-examples/tree/main)

### PR Checklist

* [ ] updated test coverage
* [X] external facing docs updated
* [X] appropriate backport labels added
* [X] not a security concern

issue.title: NET-6294 - v1 Agentless proxycfg datasource errors after v2 changes

labels.name: pr/no-changelog
labels.description: PR does not need a corresponding .changelog entry

issue.body:
### Description

This PR is intended to fix the following message when running consul in v1 kubernetes and registering a service in kubernetes which spawns a s sidecar:
```
2023-10-24T16:22:00.507Z [ERROR] agent.proxycfg: Failed to handle update from watch: kind=connect-proxy proxy=default/default/forward1-55d89888cd-5758v-forward1-sidecar-proxy service_id=default/default/forward1-55d89888cd-5758v-forward1-sidecar-proxy id=service-http-checks:default/default/forward1-55d89888cd-5758v-forward1 error="error filling agent cache: Internal cache failure: service 'forward1-55d89888cd-5758v-forward1' not in agent state"
```
The following two issues that resulted to the fix of the above were also fixed:
- `TestEnvoy/case-api-gateway-http-hostnames` is failing
- `TestHTTPRouteRetryAndTimeout` is failing

I'll make sure to follow up and dig more into why that code started panicing to begin with. I'll let someone with more domain knowledge look at the config updates.

Stop use of templated-policy and templated-policy-file simultaneously (#19389)

Resource Hook Pre-Decode Utilities (#18548)

Add some generic type hook wrappers to first decode the data

There seems to be a pattern for Validation, Mutation and Write Authorization hooks where they first need to decode the Any data before doing the domain specific work.

This PR introduces 3 new functions to generate wrappers around the other hooks to pre-decode the data into a DecodedResource and pass that in instead of the original pbresource.Resource.

This PR also updates the various catalog data types to use the new hook generators.
